Eugene Pinover focuses on representing domestic and foreign real estate companies and institutional clients.
Gene has significant experience in acquisitions, sales, joint ventures, restructuring and sophisticated financings and development projects throughout the United States. He has also represented REITs, underwriters and investors in equity offerings and debt securitizations.
Gene has been involved in the acquisition of more than 20 million square feet of New York City office buildings and over 50 million square feet of regional mall and shopping center transactions. He serves as an independent director at VEREIT and is a member of its audit, nominating and corporate governance committees.

























