Profile submitted by Eugene Pinover

Practice Areas 
Eugene Pinover, Chair of DLA Piper's New York Real Estate Practice, focuses on representing domestic and foreign real estate companies and institutional clients. Gene has significant experience in acquisitions, sales, joint ventures, restructuring and sophisticated financings and development projects throughout the United States. He has also represented REITs, underwriters and investors in equity offerings and debt securitizations. He serves as an independent director at VEREIT and is a member of its nominating and corporate governance committee.Professional Memberships 
American College of Real Estate LawyersPersonal 
JD, New York University School of Law; BA, Dartmouth College


















